2023-03-08

My meme

I think Everyone struggles with getting up in the early morning and my meme shows the actual mental status when a day with early morning classes and without early morning classes. As I have got 3 early morning classes in a row within a week and this is the inspiration of making this meme to show my actual feeling. I found 2 puppys photos, one is smiling and the other one just crying like me in the morning when I get up early to take a class. After that, I put all the photos together and finish off the meme.

library(magick)

# import the meme pictures and resize them

image1 <- image_read("1.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

image2 <- image_read("smile.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(200)

# create a blank background with words

crying <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 156.5, color = "#9DA19A") %>% 
  image_annotate(gravity = "center", text = "A day\nwith 8am\nclass", size = 30, font = "Times New Roman")


smile <- image_blank(width = 200, height = 200, color = "#9DA19A") %>%
  image_annotate(gravity = "center", text = "A day\nwithout 8am\nclass", size = 30, font = "Times New Roman")

# the first picture
crying_vector <- c(image1, crying) %>%
  image_append()

# the second picture
smile_vector <- c(image2, smile) %>% 
  image_append()
# stack two pictures up
c(crying_vector, smile_vector) %>% 
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# save my meme in the computer
image_write(my_meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated gif

The gif shows a amazing goal of a football game of the English Premier League. Therere plenty of gifs of some scene happened in the football game that Ive seen a lot so that I want to make my own one.

library(magick)

# create a 1:3 vector
count <- 1:3 %>% 
  as.character()

# create 3 backgrounds
b1 <- image_blank(width = 400,
            height = 250,
            color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = count[3], 
                 color = "#000000", 
                 font = "impact", 
                 gravity = "center", 
                 size = 100)


b2 <- image_blank(width = 400,
            height = 250,
            color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = count[2], 
                 color = "#000000", 
                 font = "impact", 
                 gravity = "center", size = 100)


b3 <- image_blank(width = 400,
            height = 250,
            color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = count[1], 
                 color = "#000000", 
                 font = "impact", 
                 gravity = "center", 
                 size = 100)

b4 <- image_blank(width = 400,
                  height = 250,
                  color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Ready?", 
                 color = "#000000",font = "impact",
                 gravity = "center", 
                 size = 50)


# create a background vector
blank_vector <- c(b1, b2, b3, b4)

# import all the photos
f1 <- image_read("1fps.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(500)
f2 <- image_read("2fps.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(500)
f3 <- image_read("3fps.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(500)
f4 <- image_read("4fps.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(500)
f5 <- image_read("5fps.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(500)
f6 <- image_read("6fps.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(500)
f7 <- image_read("7fps.jpg") %>% 
  image_scale(500)

goal <- image_blank(width = 400,
                    height = 250,
                    color = "#FFFFFF") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "gooooal!", 
                 color = "#000000", 
                 font = "impact", 
                 gravity = "center", 
                 size = 50)

# combine all the vectors and create the gif animation
c(blank_vector,f1, f2, f3, f4, f5, f6, f7, goal) %>% 
  image_animate(fps = 2) %>% 
  image_write("my_animation.gif")
